OL,3,CPolice apologise to family of dead
OL,4,CSomerset mother for 'unacceptable'
OL,5,Cfailures
OL,7,FThe IOPC also found Ms Faiers' family
OL,8,Fwere not told for nine days that Mr
OL,9,FScatchard had been at the property
OL,10,Fwhen she died, and were not told about
OL,11,Fhis offending history.
OL,13,FHer children only discovered he was a
OL,14,Fconvicted sex offender by searching
OL,15,Fhis name online when it was released
OL,16,Fto the media.
OL,18,FThe investigation also found police
OL,19,F"delayed" telling the family they were
OL,20,Ftreating Ms Faiers' death as
OL,21,Fsuspicious.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
