OL,3,CPolice apologise to family of dead
OL,4,CSomerset mother for 'unacceptable'
OL,5,Cfailures
OL,7,F"Similarly, we recognise the
OL,8,Fadditional distress experienced by Ms
OL,9,FFaiers' family at learning of Mr
OL,10,FScatchard's criminal record through an
OL,11,Fonline search and by not disclosing
OL,12,Fsooner he was at the address and
OL,13,Fspoken to by officers when police
OL,14,Finitially attended.
OL,16,F"This was information that should have
OL,17,Fbeen privately communicated to Mrs
OL,18,FFaiers' family in a sensitive way and
OL,19,Fat an appropriate time."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/7
